All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractPlayer
    Abstract class for the HumanPlayer and BotPlayer classes.
    AlphaPentaGo
    Represents the AlphaPentaGo AI bot that plays the game.
    AlphaPentaGoTest
    Tests AlphaPentaGo decisions in different game situations.
    Board
    Board is the class which represents the Pentago game board.
    BoardTest
    Test that checks whether the board performs like it should.
    BotPlayer
    Extends the AbstractPlayer class, implements the determineMove method by using the Monte Carlo Search Tree Algorithms.
    Client
    The Client class is the class that makes it possible for the user to connect to a server and play the Pentago game.
    ClientAndServerTest
    Test that checks whether the clients and server interact with each other in a correct manner.
    ClientHandler
    Handles the client by providing information to the server.
    DecisionEngine
    Represents the brain of the bot that helps to find best moves on the current board.
    DecisionEngineTest
    Tests extractMove function in the Decision Engine to see if Decision Engine can understand the move from 2 different board positions.
    Game
    Game is the class that can simulate a game of Pentago on your local machine.
    GeneralComputerClient
    GeneralComputerClient is a class that provides an important structure for both the NaiveComputerClient and SmartComputerClient.
    HumanPlayer
    Extends the AbstractPlayer class, implements the determineMove method by retrieving an input from the user.
    Mark
    Possible marks that players can use in the game.
    Minimax
    A minimax algorithm that can hardly compute the best possible move by brute forcing all possible combinations.
    MonteCarloTreeSearch
    Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) is a search technique in the field of Artificial Intelligence (AI).
    NaiveComputerClient
    Uses the GeneralComputerClient and the RandomBot (Naive Strategy) to play the game on server.
    Node
    Represents the node in the decision tree which is the part of MCTS algorithm.
    Pentago
    Pentago is the class that executes the methods in the class Game.
    RandomBot
    Represents the RandomBot AI bot that plays the game.
    RandomBotTest
    Test that checks whether the random bot performs correct by checking if it fills up the board.
    SendToServer
    Created thread that is able to send things to the server, while the client can simultaneously read stuff coming from the server.
    ServerApplication
    The class that has a main method to start the server.
    ServerImplementation
    Provides the fundamental behavior of the server.
    ServerTest
    Test that checks whether the server behaves as it should.
    SmartComputerClient
    Uses the GeneralComputerClient and the AlphaPentaGo (Smart Strategy) to play the game on server.
    State
    Represents the state of the particular node.
    StateTest
    Tests that checks how states work in MCTS algorithm.
    Strategy
    A strategy for the bot player in the game.
    Tree
    Represents the decision tree which is the part of MCTS algorithm.
    UCT
    Upper Confidence Bound applied to trees.
